Pan African 4th Annual Music Fashion Runway (MFR), took place in Nigeria at Lagos Continental Hotel Victoria Island on Thursday 29th November and was an epic success. The event was attended by iconic legends, celebrities, international designers and runway models and represented a natural fusion with quality star artist live  music performances The Game Changer Africa Acknowledgement  (GCAA) Award segment program, hosted by WOFAI SAMUEL presented by Ngozi Omambala, honours extraordinary individuals and creative pioneers. Read More: Nigerian Music Super Stars Perform At The Hennessy Artistry Concert African designs by internationally renowned Ade Bakare, IRE Clothings (Kunle Afolayan), Skentele by Etti, Big Ben Kilani, Steve Ray Couture and 12 other designs.